During the course various financial risks, the motives of their hedging, and financial derivatives are considered by solving practical assignments.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of different basic financial derivatives (forwards, futures, swaps and options) and their application for financial risk hedging purpose.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the course comprehends the motives of financial risk hedging; relationship between financial derivatives (forwards, futures, options, and swaps) and hedging various financial risk (equity risk, interest rate risk, commodity price risk, credit risk, liquidity risk), is able to estimate the value of derivatives and comprehends foundations of value formation of derivatives.
